Xaloon for Apache Wicket 1.5
============================

Licence
-------

Xaloon is distributed under the terms of the Apache Software Foundation
license, version 2.0. The text is included in the file LICENSE in the root
of the project.

Getting started
---------------

Required dependencies
---------------------

Add external repository to your settings.xml:

<profiles>
	<profile>
		<id>xaloon-external-repositories</id>
		<activation>
			<activeByDefault>true</activeByDefault>				
		</activation>
		<repositories>
			<repository>
				<id>jboss-repository</id>
				<url>http://repository.jboss.org/nexus/content/groups/public-jboss/</url>
			</repository>
			<repository>
				<id>EclipseLink Repo</id>
				<url>http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/download.php?r=1&amp;nf=1&amp;file=/rt/eclipselink/maven.repo</url>
			</repository>  
			<repository> 
				<id>googlecode-jqwicket</id> 
				<url>http://jqwicket.googlecode.com/svn/m2-repo/releases/</url> 
			</repository> 
			<repository>
				<id>mandubian-mvn</id>
				<url>http://mandubian-mvn.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/mandubian-mvn/repository</url>
			</repository>
		</repositories>
	</profile>
</profiles>	

These repositories include:
 - Offline dependencies for JAI;
 - Eclipselink dependencies if using eclipselink ORM instead of Hibernate;
 - JQWicket dependency;
 - Google picasa services if xaloon-wicket-plugin-gdata plugin is used to store images.
